#DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - It's a new year but make no mistake: The old problems at SAA won't simply disappear in the clouds. eNCA takes an in-depth look at the state of things at the national carrier and crunches the numbers surrounding the long-running woes SAA just can't seem to shake. SAA has decided to cancel and consolidate some flights for February. READ: SAA cancels some flights for February Up to 48 return flights will not take to the skies next month. On Tuesday, SAA received a R3.5-billion government-guaranteed loan from the Development Bank of South Africa. This after it cancelled several flights to preserve cash earlier this month. SAA has not made a profit for nearly a decade.